# Jekyll Portfolio Project Structure

This is a Jekyll-based portfolio website using the Minimal Mistakes theme hosted on GitHub Pages.

## Key Configuration Files
- [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) - Main Jekyll configuration with site settings, author info, and theme configuration
- [Gemfile](mdc:Gemfile) - Ruby dependencies including GitHub Pages and Minimal Mistakes theme
- [index.markdown](mdc:index.markdown) - Homepage with splash layout and overlay image

## Site Structure
- **Content Pages**: [_pages/](mdc:_pages/) directory contains main site pages (about, portfolio, blog)
- **Blog Posts**: [_posts/](mdc:_posts/) directory contains blog entries with date-prefixed filenames
- **Navigation**: [_data/navigation.yml](mdc:_data/navigation.yml) defines the main site navigation menu
- **Assets**: [assets/](mdc:assets/) contains images, CSS, and JavaScript files

## Theme Integration
- Uses Minimal Mistakes Jekyll theme (remote_theme: "mmistakes/minimal-mistakes@4.24.0")
- Custom SCSS in [_sass/](mdc:_sass/) directory with theme overrides
- Theme layouts available: splash, single, archive, collection, etc.

## Author Profile
- Bio photo: [assets/images/bio-photo.jpg](mdc:assets/images/bio-photo.jpg)
- Author info configured in [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) under 'author' section
- Social links for GitHub and LinkedIn configured